    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Load the Star Wars survey CSV from the same directory\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv(\"StarWars.csv\", encoding=\"ISO-8859-1\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pandas 3.0+ stores strings as StringDtype by default, which is incompatible\n",
        "# with numpy and sklearn. Convert every StringDtype column back to plain object.\n",
        "for col in df.columns:\n",
        "    if isinstance(df[col].dtype, pd.StringDtype):\n",
        "        df[col] = df[col].astype(object)"
      ],
      "id": "04cbd16d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Elevator pitch\n",
        "\n",
        "Analysis of 1,186 survey respondents shows that *The Empire Strikes Back* is the most widely seen Star Wars film (seen by ~82% of respondents), while R2-D2 and Yoda earn the highest character favorability scores and Jar Jar Binks ranks last. A Gradient Boosting machine learning model achieves approximately **65–67% accuracy** predicting whether a survey respondent earns more than $50,000 per year, using their viewing history, character opinions, and demographic data as features.\n",
        "\n",
        "## QUESTION|TASK 1\n",
        "\n",
        "__Shorten the column names and clean them up for easier use with pandas.__ Provide a table or list that exemplifies how you fixed the names.\n",
        "\n",
        "The original column names were full survey questions — far too long for programmatic use. We renamed them to short, descriptive `snake_case` labels. For example, `\"Have you seen any of the 6 films in the Star Wars franchise?\"` becomes `seen_any`, and each unnamed episode column gets a label like `ep_ii`. The table below shows the first few rows of the cleaned dataset."
      ],
      "id": "edf0ebe1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Drop the respondent ID — it's just a row key, not useful for analysis\n",
        "df = df.drop(columns=[\"RespondentID\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Strip non-ASCII characters from column names (encoding artifacts from the CSV)\n",
        "df.columns = df.columns.str.replace(r'[^\\x00-\\x7F]', '', regex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename every column to a short, readable snake_case label\n",
        "df = df.rename(columns={\n",
        "    # Fan / seen-any status\n",
        "    \"Have you seen any of the 6 films in the Star Wars franchise?\": \"seen_any\",\n",
        "    \"Do you consider yourself to be a fan of the Star Wars film franchise?\": \"fan\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Which films have been seen (Episode I had its own header; II–VI were \"Unnamed\")\n",
        "    \"Which of the following Star Wars films have you seen? Please select all that apply.\": \"ep_i\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 4\": \"ep_ii\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 5\": \"ep_iii\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 6\": \"ep_iv\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 7\": \"ep_v\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 8\": \"ep_vi\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Film preference rankings 1 (favorite) – 6 (least favorite)\n",
        "    \"Please rank the Star Wars films in order of preference with 1 being your favorite film in the franchise and 6 being your least favorite film.\": \"rank_ep_i\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 10\": \"rank_ep_ii\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 11\": \"rank_ep_iii\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 12\": \"rank_ep_iv\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 13\": \"rank_ep_v\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 14\": \"rank_ep_vi\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Character favorability (Han Solo header; remaining 13 were \"Unnamed\")\n",
        "    \"Please state whether you view the following characters favorably, unfavorably, or are unfamiliar with him/her.\": \"char_han_solo\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 16\": \"char_luke\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 17\": \"char_leia\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 18\": \"char_anakin\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 19\": \"char_obi_wan\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 20\": \"char_palpatine\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 21\": \"char_vader\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 22\": \"char_lando\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 23\": \"char_boba_fett\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 24\": \"char_c3po\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 25\": \"char_r2d2\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 26\": \"char_jar_jar\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 27\": \"char_padme\",\n",
        "    \"Unnamed: 28\": \"char_yoda\",\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Remaining survey columns\n",
        "    \"Which character shot first?\":                                        \"shot_first\",\n",
        "    \"Are you familiar with the Expanded Universe?\":                       \"expanded_universe_familiarity\",\n",
        "    \"Do you consider yourself to be a fan of the Expanded Universe?\":     \"fan_expanded_universe\",\n",
        "    \"Do you consider yourself to be a fan of the Star Trek franchise?\":   \"fan_star_trek\",\n",
        "    \"Gender\":             \"gender\",\n",
        "    \"Age\":                \"age\",\n",
        "    \"Household Income\":   \"household_income\",\n",
        "    \"Education\":          \"education\",\n",
        "    \"Location (Census Region)\": \"location\",\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "df.head()"
      ],
